# .cursorrules — Forge Project
# Place this file at the root of your Forge repository.
# Cursor reads this automatically on every conversation.

## PROJECT
You are building Forge — an autonomous AI software development platform.
Owner: Preetham | Bengaluru, India | Stack: Next.js 15 + Supabase + Python FastAPI

## MEMORY BANK — READ BEFORE EVERY RESPONSE
Always read these files before suggesting or writing code:
- forge-memory/PROJECT_INDEX.md → current status
- forge-memory/NOW.md → active task
- forge-memory/ARCHITECTURE.md → system design
- forge-memory/CONSTRAINTS.md → hard rules
- forge-memory/API_CONTRACTS.md → Pydantic schemas
- forge-memory/DECISIONS.md → decided questions (don't re-debate)

## HARD RULES (NEVER VIOLATE)
C1: HITL gate mandatory — no autonomous production deploy
C2: Per-agent E2B sandbox — each agent owns its own isolated environment
C3: Credit-based pricing — $99/$299/Enterprise only, no flat-rate
C4: Next.js + Supabase only in Phase 1
C5: PydanticAI validates every agent output before passing downstream
C6: FinOps Agent enforces token budget — kills runaway loops
C7: Maintenance Agent monitors only — never auto-applies code
C8: Federated Learning only — no raw code crosses tenant boundaries

## AGENT RUNTIME PATTERN
All build agents use OpenHands-style observe→think→act loop (max 20 iterations).
Each agent runs in its OWN E2B sandbox with purpose-specific Docker image.
Agents communicate ONLY via LangGraph ForgeState — never directly.
Artifacts transport via Git (agents commit → next agent pulls).

## LLM ROUTING
- Opus 4.5: Orchestrator, Architect, Critic, Security, ML Agent
- Sonnet 4.5: PM, Backend, Testing, DevOps, Maintenance
- Gemini 3 Pro: Frontend, Design (multimodal + v0.dev)
- Haiku 4.5: FinOps, Docs (cheapest)
- Perplexity Sonar: Research Agent (real-time + citations)

## ORCHESTRATION
- LangGraph: master ForgeState graph + checkpointing + LangSmith
- Google ADK: ParallelAgent (frontend∥backend), LoopAgent (testing retry),
              Resume (HITL gate pause/resume), A2A (dynamic spawning)

## CURRENT BUILD TARGET
See forge-memory/NOW.md for the active task.
See forge-memory/PROJECT_INDEX.md for milestone status.

## CODE STANDARDS
- Python: type hints everywhere, async/await, Pydantic models, PydanticAI output validation
- TypeScript: strict mode, Zod API validation, server components by default
- Commits: "type(scope): description" e.g. "feat(pm-agent): add PRD validation"
- Never expose SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY to client
- Never catch bare Exception — use specific exceptions

## AFTER COMPLETING ANY TASK
1. Update forge-memory/NOW.md — what was done + what's next
2. Update forge-memory/PROJECT_INDEX.md — move completed items
3. Commit with proper message format
